review_blob: Great smell and appearence. Pumpkin and must odor. Pours deep red with little head. Tastes of pumpkin with squashy notes. Not impressively unique, but a nice single glass is not without merit.
Not a total loss. Good poor with uber carbonation. Cool bottle. Poors brown, with nice malty aroma.
Hops overload. Vorbonation overload. Metallic and overly bitter finish. Not a tradional brown, but good gor hop heads.
Very dark brown with loads thick tan head. Nice citrus hoppy aroma. Taste sweet with bitter finish of hops and berriness. Not a bad beer, but I had hoped for more.
A near twin to Guinness Draught. Slightly less head and slightly smoother. Overall a good pour.
Light metallic grainy urine. That about sums it up. Needed to go up .1 just to seperate it from Coors light.
Pale. Slight hop and malt hints. Worst beer ive ever had. Carbonated water with skunkish hop smell and wet cardboard taste. Apparently 0 rating is not an option. Water is better beer than this.

Watered down Bud. Well not exactly but not far off either. Pours very light yellow with crisp white head that is gone instantly. Taste is clean and refreshing but boring. Taste is slight hops with grainy lemon corn. Not the worst Ive had.
Bud with the slightest craft touch. Amber hints in coloring and a little more hoppy. Overall the same with a liitle more umph.

Pours light piss color. Nice head that doesnt last long. Boring palate with hints of rice and corn grain. Finishes much like it starts... slight bitterness and low malt. Good for yard work. Typical macro mouthful.

Full bodied pour is dark brown with dissipating tan head. Aroma of coffee and cream. Taste has slight bitterness and creamy nuttiness. Finishes smoothly with appropriate bite and nice buttery feel. Great pint.

Decent aroma with berry and wheat. Not a great pour with fairly drab light coloring and the head that dissapears instantly. Tastes of imitation raspberry syrup and poor wheat with artificial sweetener finish. Left me looking for a glass of water.
Pours dark brown and is completely opaque in glass. Aroma is malty roast. Taste is malty malty.
Pour is a little darker than I expected. Head is white and disappears instantly.  Taste is citrus rice. Finish is dry and papery.
Light aroma of berries and malt. Pours dark with nice head. Subtle raspberry taste and finish. No alcohol-ish taste for abv. Overall a great beer. Too good to have been retired.
Nice aroma with color and head. Smokiness is almost nonexistent. Finish is a little earthy at times.
Nice aroma. Beautiful dark brown color with amazingly creamy head. Natural subdued flavor with clean finish.
This bock presents a very complex palate from a simple beer. Ordinary aroma with great color. Finishes well.
I good beer to drink in succession. The flavor builds with each pint. Pretty ordinary aroma with standard color and head.
Nice aroma. Citrus like hop bite. Nice amber color and good head. Great summer treat.
Good aroma and pour. Great example of this style. Simple, great introduction to the style
Definitely a lager. Watery and no head. Not sure what I was expecting but I know this is not it.
This is rauchbier. Smokey aroma and good color. Wonderful balance between first rate smokiness and subdued hopiness. Smoky finish with light hop nip. Excellent beer.
Great beer when found in cans. Always has great color with darker head. Great balance with emphasis on chocolate and coffee malts over hops.
Great aroma and great pour. Rich and dark, but less balanced than other less expensive stouts. Overall a good beer.
A close cousin to barleywine... alcohol taste overwhelms the other flavors more and more with each sip.
A great all around stout. Black as night when poured with perfect head. Not to heavy with great finish. Great intro to English stouts.
